id.description: The token ID. This is a required field in the ``token`` object.

password.description:
The password of the user. Required if you include the
``passwordCredentials`` object. If you do not provide a password
credentials, you must provide a token.

passwordCredentials.description:
A ``passwordCredentials`` object. To authenticate, you must provide
either a user ID and password or a token.

tenantId.description:
The tenant ID. Both the ``tenantId`` and ``tenantName`` attributes
are optional, but should not be specified together. If both
attributes are specified, the server responds with a ``400`` ``Bad
Request`` .

tenantName.description:
The tenant name. Both the ``tenantId`` and ``tenantName``
attributes are optional, but should not be specified together. If
both attributes are specified, the server responds with a ``400``
``Bad Request`` .

token.description:
A ``token`` object. Required if you do not provide password
credentials.

username.description:
The user name. Required if you include the ``passwordCredentials``
object. If you do not provide a password credentials, you must
provide a token.

description.description: The description of the tenant. If not set, this value is ``null`` .

enabled.description: Indicates whether the tenant is enabled or disabled.

endpoints.description:
One or more ``endpoints`` objects. Each object shows the
``adminURL`` , ``region`` , ``internalURL`` , ``id`` , and
``publicURL`` for the endpoint.

expires.description:
The date and time when the token expires.

The date and time stamp format is `ISO 8601
<https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/ISO_8601>`_ :

::

   CCYY-MM-DDThh:mm:ss±hh:mm

The ``±hh:mm`` value, if included, is the time zone as an offset
from UTC.

For example, ``2015-08-27T09:49:58-05:00``.

A ``null`` value indicates that the token never expires.

issued_at.description:
The date and time when the token was issued.

The date and time stamp format is `ISO 8601
<https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/ISO_8601>`_ :

::

   CCYY-MM-DDThh:mm:ss±hh:mm

The ``±hh:mm`` value, if included, is the time zone as an offset
from UTC.

For example, ``2015-08-27T09:49:58-05:00``.

user.description:
A ``user`` object, which shows the ``username`` , ``roles_links`` ,
``id`` , ``roles`` , and ``name`` .

enabled.description: Indicates whether the user is enabled (true) or disabled (false).
Indicates whether the user is enabled (true) or disabled (false).

next.description: Moves to the next item in the list.

previous.description: Moves to the previous item in the list.

enabled.description: Indicates whether the user is enabled (true) or disabled (false).

/v2.0/tokens.description:
A REST interface provides client authentication by using the POST
method with ``v2.0/tokens`` as the path. Include a payload of
credentials in the body.

The Identity API is a RESTful web service. It is the entry point to
all service APIs. To access the Identity API, you must know its
URL.

Each REST request against the Identity Service requires the ``X
-Auth-Token`` header. Clients obtain this token and the URL
endpoints for other service APIs by supplying their valid
credentials to the authentication service.

If the authentication token has expired, this call returns the HTTP
``401`` status code.

If the token specified in the request body has expired, this call
returns the HTTP ``404`` status code.

The Identity API treats expired tokens as no longer valid tokens.

The deployment determines how long expired tokens are stored.
